🚀 1. Connect to Your EC2 (Ubuntu)
ssh -i ~/m.pem ubuntu@<your-public-ip>
🔹 2. Update System
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
🔹 3. Install Python & Pip
sudo apt install python3-pip python3-venv -y

Check:

python3 --version
pip3 --version
🔹 4. Create Virtual Environment (Recommended ✅)
python3 -m venv mlflow-env
source mlflow-env/bin/activate
🔹 5. Install MLflow
pip install mlflow

Verify:

mlflow --version
🔹 6. mlflow server \
--host 0.0.0.0 \
--port 5000 \
--allowed-hosts '*'
🌐 7. Access MLflow UI in Browser

Open:

http://<your-ec2-public-ip>:5000
🔥 IMPORTANT (Don’t Skip)
Allow Port 5000 in Security Group

Go to:
👉 Amazon EC2 → Security Group

Add inbound rule:

Type: Custom TCP
Port: 5000
Source: 0.0.0.0/0
